					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-768664#post-2031748</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-768664/scp-1629#post-2031748</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 14 May 2014 02:26:14 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>dankaar</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1790336</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>A bit off base. The Locked Box Test is a good rule of thumb, but can't apply to everything.</p> <p>There are two ways something is considered Safe. The first is the obvious one: if it only does something when you metaphorically poke it, it's Safe.</p> <p>The other way something is Safe is predictability. If you can predict what will happen when it does X 100% of the time, and if the Containment Procedures give a 100% chance of keeping it secure so long as they are followed, it's Safe.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-768664#post-2031742</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-768664/scp-1629#post-2031742</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 14 May 2014 02:08:22 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>5thEarth</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1875714</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Newbie here, so I may be way off base with this, but I think this might qualify as Euclid.</p> <p>If the cabinet isn't given access to the atmosphere at frequent, unpredictable intervals, the plane starts blowing holes through things. You can't exactly lock it away and forget about it unless you don't mind turning your building into swiss cheese. There's always the option of just leaving it outside all the time, but that's not exactly containment.</p> <p>Also, it might be a good idea to store it in a no-fly zone, to reduce the chance of aircraft strikes.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
